{"add":{"doc":{"id":"c1d623e571f3e5ba80009e161f95852050136b1e3431f1eda52183d0e98f8e50","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Kitchen_timer.jpg/220px-Kitchen_timer.jpg","previous":[],"after":["A timer is a specialized type of clock for measuring time intervals.[1] By function timers can be categorized to two main types. A timer which counts upwards from zero for measuring elapsed time is often called a stopwatch; a device which counts down from a specified time interval is more usually called a timer[1] or a countdown timer. A simple example for this type is an hourglass. By working method timers have two main groups: Hardware and Software timers."]}}}